    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dull yellow-brown, transparent pigment created when precipitated on an inert base from crystallized orange-brown needles made from a dilute glacial acetic acid solution. Developed in 1887 by R. Nietzki, it became the first azo mordant dye.</Note_Text>
